{
  "doc_id": "18667",
  "text": "Coster et al. [CITATION_1] believed that the gas in the Pande field was microbial (they called it \"immature\") and sourced from the Lower Grudja mudstones. However, our isotope data indicate that the gas in the Pande field is a pure thermogenic gas and very mature. Lower Grudja mudstones are not a likely candidate for source rocks in the basin because they are not sufficiently mature.",
  "correct_citation": {
